cs.NI, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.CV

The paper discusses the use of machine learning techniques for improving the intelligence and autonomy of optical networks, which are a critical component of communication systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of ML for optical network control and resource management, which falls under the category of cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the paper provides a tutorial on ML algorithms and paradigms, which is related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the use of ML for optical network monitoring, which can be related to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
